From: Jan Maslak <jan.maslak@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Sep 2025 14:43:28 +0000
Subject: fixup! drm/xe/vma: Modify new_vma to accept struct
 xe_vma_mem_attr as parameter

Inside xe_vma_create() assert that attr isn't NULL, since it's
dereferenced later on in the function.

Signed-off-by: Jan Maslak <jan.maslak@intel.com>
(backported from commit d4bfdaa650acd32c5a8be18c5b01890550ba200a drm-tip-eudebug)
Signed-off-by: Pravalika Gurram <pravalika.gurram@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_vm.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_vm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_vm.c
index ca7c35e84..dce2f45bb 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_vm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_vm.c
@@ -1004,6 +1004,7 @@ static struct xe_vma *xe_vma_create(struct xe_vm *vm,
 
 	xe_assert(vm->xe, start < end);
 	xe_assert(vm->xe, end < vm->size);
+	xe_assert(vm->xe, attr);
 
 	/*
 	 * Allocate and ensure that the xe_vma_is_userptr() return
